  "market_context": "NQ1! 15-minute chart spanning multiple sessions in early October 2023. Price action moves through Asia, London, and New York AM/PM kill zones with price oscillating between ~14820 and ~15040, providing a textbook session-by-session delivery sequence.",
  "key_observation": "Across each kill zone, price swept liquidity, displaced back into range creating fair value gaps and order blocks, then respected standard deviation projections from the London manipulation leg, hitting the 2–2.5 deviation target during New York AM.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify that Asia low was swept and price displaced back into the range, leaving a fair value gap expected to act as support on retest toward Asia high.",
    "Step 2: Note price aggressively pushed out then back into range; apply box setup logic by extending previous highs to anticipate resistance, which holds, while a new fair value gap forms.",
    "Step 3: Observe price retracing into the new fair value gap with bodies respecting; expect continuation through the older fair value gap below.",
    "Step 4: Identify displacement lower through up-close candles into an important level, forming an order block as price closes below the series of up-close candles.",
    "Step 5: Project standard deviations from the London manipulation high to low; confirm price entered the 2–2.5 standard deviation zone where retracement/reversal is anticipated.",
    "Step 6: Mark OTE from London high to current low; confirm overlapping confluence between OTE zone and the old fair value gap as the entry area.",
    "Step 7: Plan entry in the old fair value gap with stop above London high, targeting the prior low or the 4 standard deviation extension.",
    "Step 8: Confirm New York AM concluded by hitting the London manipulation projection target.",
    "Step 9: Mark up-close candles into the PM session; observe close below the series, signalling change in state of delivery for end-of-day continuation lower."
  ],
  "outcome": "Projection from London manipulation was reached during New York AM session; PM session continued lower after closing through up-close candles.",
  "lessons": "Each kill zone delivers a repeatable sequence: liquidity sweep, displacement, fair value gap/order block creation, and standard deviation/OTE confluence. Aligning London manipulation projections with PD arrays produces high-probability New York entries.",
